SQLDatabase - Interface in com.stardevllc.stardata.api.interfaces
This class represents a SQLDatabase
Please be aware, that Databases must already exist, this library will not create databases
Normal Database actions happen in their own connection to prevent memory leaks.
SQLDatabaseRegistry - Class in com.stardevllc.stardata.sql.objects
This class is how SQLDatabase's are managed and initialized within this library
You can create databases using the Database Constructors or by using the factory style methods in this class.
If you create databases through the constructors, you still have to register them here using the register(Database) methods
Databases must already exist in the MySQL Database.

StarSQL - Class in com.stardevllc.stardata.sql
This library allows a developer to use Java Classes to represent MySQL Tables.
You cannot do everything in MySQL with this library, it was created as a means to prevent manual saving and loading of data to database tables and prevent errors related to building statements.
There are plans on a complete rewrite of this library into a new library that will not just handle MySQL but some other storage methods like JSON, and Yaml
This library is designed to be interacted with in java code, however it is also done in a way where the developer can manage their own files for configuration.
I have done my best to document this library thoroughly, with improvements being made to the library and documentation
The entry point to using this library is the SQLDatabaseRegistry class.
